-- Turkish Stocks: Ar Tarim, Fenerbahce, Turkcell Shares Are Active
-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 2012-06-25T15:56:36Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-25/turkish-stocks-ar-tarim-turkcell-shares-are-active-in-istanbul.html
Turkey’s benchmark  ISE National 100
Index (XU100)  fell for the first time in five days, dropping 1.6 percent
to 59,479.36 at the close in Istanbul, the most in a month.  The following shares were active. Stock symbols are in
parentheses.  Ar Tarim Organik Gida AS (ARTOG)  , an organic agriculture
company, rose to the highest level since its listing June 1,
jumping 18 percent to 5.84 liras, after saying it bought farm
land in Diyarbakir province in southeast Turkey to expand its
activities.  Fenerbahce Sportif Hizmetler Sanayi & Ticaret AS (FENER)  , the listed arm of Istanbul soccer club Fenerbahce, soared
for a second day, adding 12 percent to 55 liras, after the team
said June 22 it had been cleared to play in Europe’s Champions
League Tournament. The shares have increased 31 percent in the
past five days.  Turkcell Iletisim Hizmetleri AS (TCELL)  , Turkey’s
largest mobile phone company advanced as much as 2.3 percent
before closing 0.5 percent up at 8.72 liras. Capital newspaper
reported Turkcell may bid for Globul, the Bulgarian mobile-phone
unit of Athens-based Hellenic Telecommunications Organization
SA. Turkcell said there is no decision on a potential
acquisition of Globul.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Harvey in Istanbul at 
